# - Frank Sweeter

This module is used to manage selinux stuff. Currently we mainly 
use it to manage selinux stuff on gentoo, however there are as well
some funtions for other distros.

ToDo: Use native puppet types, when they will be integrated

# defines

# define selinux::loadmodule ($location) 

location = location of the pp (eg. /usr/share/selinux/strict/logrotate.pp)
this one is used to load certain modules

# selinux::module

use this function to deploy a certain module, it is identified by $name
